verschillende mogelijkheden
http://wiki.debian.org/EmDebian/CrossDebootstrap

1) Download the necessary .deb packages from a repository.
2) Unpack then into the target directory.
   multistrap -a armel -d /media/Root -f multistrap.conf
			[General]
			unpack=true
			debootstrap=Grip
			aptsources=Grip
			cleanup=true

			[Grip]
			packages=ntpdate libqtcore4 libqtgui4 libqt4-network libqt4-xml libqt4-webkit openssh-server apt libterm-readline-perl-perl vim xserver-xorg xserver-xorg-input-evdev xserver-xorg-video-imx
			source=http://www.emdebian.org/grip
			keyring=emdebian-archive-keyring
			suite=squeeze
3) Chroot into the target directory.
   cp /etc/resolv.conf /media/Root/etc
   chroot /media/Root

4) Run the installation and configuration scripts from each package, finishing the setup. 
   dpkg --configure -a

*) emdebian key toevoegen en packages updaten
   apt-get update
   apt-get upgrade

*) SeriÃ«le terminal aanzetten
	 /etc/inittab:		T0:23:respawn:/sbin/getty -L ttymxc0 115200 vt100
	 /etc/securetty:	ttymxc0

*) fstab
		# /etc/fstab: static file system information.
		#
		# Use 'blkid -o value -s UUID' to print the universally unique identifier
		# for a device; this may be used with UUID= as a more robust way to name
		# devices that works even if disks are added and removed. See fstab(5).
		#
		# <file system>                                 <dir>           <type>  <options> <dump> <pass>

		# System mounts
		devpts                                          /dev/pts        devpts  defaults 0 0
		shm                                             /dev/shm        tmpfs   nodev,nosuid 0 0
		tmpfs                                           /tmp            tmpfs   defaults,noatime,mode=1777 0 0
		proc                                            /proc           proc    nodev,noexec,nosuid 0 0

		# Data mounts (SDHC mode)
		rootfs                                          /               auto    defaults,noatime 0 1

		# Data mounts (SSD mode)
		#/dev/sda2                                      /               auto    defaults 0 1
		#/dev/sda1                                      /boot           auto    defaults 0 2
		#/dev/sda3                                      none            swap    defaults 0 0

*) Root wachtwoord instellen
		passwd
